## What Copilot must NOT do in this repo

- **Do not author code outside an active ticket's feature branch.** Branches follow `feature/<TICKET-ID>-<scope>`.
- **Do not commit pre-squash SHAs** in any lifecycle artifact. Always cite merge-commit SHAs (reachable from `main`) or use narrative paraphrase.
- **Do not bypass the verify gate.** `/commit` refuses unless `/verify` has produced a non-blocking verdict.
- **Do not introduce new dependencies** without justifying them in the plan.
- **Do not edit `forge.config.yml`** to make a check pass — fix the underlying state.

## What Copilot SHOULD do

- Read the active plan in `.lifecycle/artifacts/<module>/plans/<sprint>/<TICKET>_<scope>.md` before suggesting code.
- Reference workspace symbolic refs (`<workspace.backend_root>`, `<workspace.frontend_root>`, etc.) — the LangGraph engine resolves these from `forge.config.yml` at interrupt time.
- Mirror existing patterns in the codebase rather than introducing novel idioms.
- Preserve the project's English-only convention in code + commits + lifecycle artifacts.

